\f0\b\fs46 \cf0 Iceberg Wedge Salad with Warm Bacon Dressing\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs26 \cf2 Serves: 
\b0 \cf0 4 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 head iceberg lettuce\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 slices bacon\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons brown {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sugar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 sugar}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup red {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/wine/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 wine}} vinegar\
{\listtext	\'95	}Salt and freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 hard-boiled egg, finely chopped\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Remove the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/core/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 core}} from the lettuce and cut into 4 quarters. Arrange on serving plates and set aside.\
\
In a small skillet saute bacon until {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/crisp/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 crisp}}. Remove from skillet, to a plate lined with a paper bag or paper towels. Once cooled, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chop/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chop}} into small pieces and add to a small bowl. In the skillet over low heat, add the brown sugar, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/vinegar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 vinegar}} and salt and pepper, to taste. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whisk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Whisk}} together until combined and sugar is completely dissolved. Stir in the egg and bacon and season with salt and pepper, to taste. Pour over the top of the iceberg wedges and serve immediately.}